text: Smyrna is an unincorporated community in Grant County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Smyrna was established in 1911, and remained in operation until 1964. The community was named after the ancient city of Smyrna. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Grant County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Smyrna, Washington
